                   "biography":  {
                                     "value":  "\u003cp\u003eÃšrn is a Bundingsteinn diver \u0026mdash; one of the coastal kinship specialists who navigate the flooded reef-caves and drowned passages beneath the Singing Islands shelf. He is compact and strong-necked, with calluses on both palms from years of pulling through current. He smells of brine regardless of how long he has been ashore.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHe hires out as a guide to the drowned sections. He knows the tides better than the moons do, he says. This is almost true.\u003c/p\u003e",
                                     "director":  "\u003csection class=\"secret\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSQ1 \u0026mdash; THE DROWNED MESSENGER\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHe/him. Bundingsteinn diver and guide. Casual manner, very precise when the situation requires it. He approaches the party near Beat 11 (Act 2) or at a coastal waystation if the party lingers near the Singing Islands shelf.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTHE QUEST:\u003c/strong\u003e A Bundingsteinn relay-swimmer drowned three days ago in a flooded reef-cave near the Singing Islands. She was carrying a sealed intelligence satchel \u0026mdash; reports on Dreyfus\u0027s coastal movements, intercepted by Bundingsteinn observers. The current swept the body into the cave system. Ãšrn needs the party\u0027s help recovering the satchel (the swimmer\u0027s body he will handle himself, he says quietly). The cave is passable for thirty minutes at low tide; longer requires underwater navigation that non-Bundingsteinn will find difficult.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eREWARD:\u003c/strong\u003e The satchel\u0027s contents \u0026mdash; intelligence on Dreyfus\u0027s coastal supply chain and the location of his northern staging point. Also: Ãš rn\u0027s goodwill, which is worth something at the Singing Islands and along the Bundingsteinn coastal waypoints through the rest of Act 2.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUNDERWATER ENCOUNTER:\u003c/strong\u003e Something moved into the reef-cave after the swimmer\u0027s death. See the SQ1 encounter specification for details.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIN COMBAT:\u003c/strong\u003e Ãšrn is competent but not eager. He fights with a short-handled harpoon tool (treat as a dagger, Agility +3). In water, he has advantage on all Agility rolls and can use the environment to channel or block enemies. Out of water he relies on the party.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/section\u003e",
